{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:job.40",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 40,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 40",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 40 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:1",
      "text": "And the Lord answering Job out of the whirlwind, said:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:2",
      "text": "Gird up thy loins like a man: I will ask thee, and do thou tell me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:3",
      "text": "Wilt thou make void my judgment: and condemn me, that thou mayst be justified?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:4",
      "text": "And hast thou an arm like God, and canst thou thunder with a voice like him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:5",
      "text": "Clothe thyself with beauty, and set thyself up on high, and be glorious, and put on goodly garments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:6",
      "text": "Scatter the proud in thy indignation, and behold every arrogant man, and humble him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:7",
      "text": "Look on all that are proud, and confound them, and crush the wicked in their place,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:8",
      "text": "Hide them in the dust together, and plunge their faces into the pit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:9",
      "text": "Then I will confess that thy right hand is able to save thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:10",
      "text": "Behold behemoth whom I made with thee, he eateth grass like an ox.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:11",
      "text": "His strength is in his loins, and his force in the navel of his belly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:12",
      "text": "He setteth up his tail like a cedar, the sinews of his testicles are wrapped together.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:13",
      "text": "His bones are like pipes of brass, his gristle like plates of iron.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:14",
      "text": "He is the beginning of the ways of God, who made him, he will apply his sword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:15",
      "text": "To him the mountains bring forth grass: there all the beasts of the field shall play.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:16",
      "text": "He sleepeth under the shadow, in the covert of the reed, and in moist places.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:17",
      "text": "The shades cover his shadow, the willows of the brook shall compass him about.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:18",
      "text": "Behold, he will drink up a river, and not wonder: and he trusteth that the Jordan may run into his mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:19",
      "text": "In his eyes as with a hook he shall take him, and bore through his nostrils with stakes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:20",
      "text": "Canst thou draw out the leviathan with a hook, or canst thou tie his tongue with a cord?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:21",
      "text": "Canst thou put a ring in his nose, or bore through his jaw with a buckle?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:22",
      "text": "Will he make many supplications to thee, or speak soft words to thee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:23",
      "text": "Will he make a covenant with thee, and wilt thou take him to be a servant for ever?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:24",
      "text": "Shalt thou play with him as with a bird, or tie him up for thy handmaids?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:25",
      "text": "Shall friends cut him in pieces, shall merchants divide him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:26",
      "text": "Wilt thou fill nets with his skin, and the cabins of fishes with his head?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:27",
      "text": "Lay thy hand upon him: remember the battle, and speak no more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.40.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:28",
      "text": "Behold his hope shall fail him, and in the sight of all he shall be cast down.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
